{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"02761f5b-e853-4474-ba12-23773a68b019","content":"Here's what you need to know for .NET MAUI on .NET 10:\n\n**`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` — ✅ Correct**\n\nThis is the right approach. Make sure you include the namespace:\n```xml\nxmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n```\n\n**`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on a Grid — ❌ Not a real property**\n\nThere is no `IgnoreSafeArea` property in .NET MAUI. That tutorial is incorrect or outdated.\n\n**For a background image behind the safe area**, the typical pattern is:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"...\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\">\n    <Grid>\n        <!-- Background fills entire screen including behind notch -->\n        <Image Source=\"bg.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n        \n        <!-- Content respects safe area via padding -->\n        <Grid Padding=\"{OnPlatform iOS='44,0,34,0'}\">\n            <!-- Your content here -->\n        </Grid>\n    </Grid>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nAlternatively, keep `UseSafeArea=\"True\"` and use negative margins on the background image to extend it beyond the safe area. The key point: safe area is controlled at the **page level**, not per-view.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"360c0ee9-e604-42e5-b43a-831db2a174a3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository doesn't have specific content about MAUI safe area handling. Let me answer from my knowledge about .NET MAUI safe area APIs.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the safe area handling has evolved:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - This is the iOS platform-specific property from Xamarin.Forms / early .NET MAUI. In .NET MAUI, it's accessed via the `Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific` namespace. The XAML would use:\n   ```xml\n   xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n   ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"\n   ```\n\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` - This is NOT a standard .NET MAUI property. In .NET MAUI, there's no built-in `IgnoreSafeArea` property on layouts like Grid.\n\nFor .NET 10 MAUI, `Page.UseSafeArea` is the iOS platform-specific way to control safe area behavior, but there's no direct equivalent `IgnoreSafeArea` property for layouts—you'd need to handle safe area insets through other means like padding or margin adjustments. I need to clarify what's actually available in .NET MAUI—`IgnoreSafeArea` isn't a standard property on Grid or other layouts, so the approach would be to disable `UseSafeArea` on the page itself and then manage padding on individual content areas instead.","outputTokens":1146,"requestId":"A857:2A55B4:7384F0:856593:69FBE63E"},"id":"38b6109b-6c0f-470c-9ab9-5231c4715fe3","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:09:38.437Z","parentId":"d2a9f118-5c12-45bb-acb0-b1e4064cc048"}
